Title: Spectrum of $\gamma$-Fluids: A Statistical Derivation
Authors: J. A. E. Carrillo, J. A. S. Lima and A. Maia Jr
Comments: 7 pages, LaTex, no figures
Journal-ref: Int.J.Theor.Phys. 35 (1996) 2013-2018
\\
  The spectrum of massless bosonic and fermionic fluids satisfying the equation
of state $p=(\gamma-1)\rho$ is derived using elementary statistical methods. As
a limiting case, the Lorentz invariant spectrum of the vacuum ($\gamma=0,
p=-\rho$) is deduced. These results are in agreement with our earlier
derivation for bosons using thermodynamics and semiclassical considerations.
